msgstr "80, 0x80, ou E9"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:109
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "A single hex byte (with or without `0x`). Latin-1 is strictly 1 byte = 1 code point."
msgstr "Un seul octet hex (avec ou sans `0x`). Latin-1 est strictement 1 octet = 1 code point."

#: lib/app_web/components/sandbox_components.ex:99
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Big Endian (BE)"
msgstr "Big Endian (BE)"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:102
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:128
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:143
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:167
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Byte"
msgstr "Octet"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:96
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Code point `%{cp}` fits in 16 significant bits."
msgstr "Le code point `%{cp}` tient sur 16 bits significatifs."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_encode.ex:140
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Code point `%{cp}` fits in exactly 8 bits. Latin-1 makes the code point value coincide with the byte value: no marker, no splitting."
msgstr "Le code point `%{cp}` tient sur 8 bits exactement. Latin-1 fait coïncider la valeur du code point avec celle de l'octet : pas de marqueur, pas de découpe."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:103
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Code point `%{cp}` is in the ASCII range: its byte `0x00` → `0x7F` reads straight into binary (8 bits, high bit `0`)."
msgstr "Le code point `%{cp}` est dans la plage ASCII : son octet `0x00` → `0x7F` se lit directement en binaire (8 bits, bit haut à `0`)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:117
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Code point `%{cp}` is in the Latin-1 Supplement range (`U+00A0` → `U+00FF`): its byte matches the code point value, written as 8 bits."
msgstr "Le code point `%{cp}` est dans la plage Latin-1 supplément (`U+00A0` → `U+00FF`) : son octet est identique à la valeur du code point, à convertir en binaire sur 8 bits."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:110
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Code point `%{cp}` isn't in an identity range. Look up the [CP1252^Code Page 1252] table to find its byte between `0x80` and `0x9F`, then convert to binary."
msgstr "Le code point `%{cp}` n'est pas dans une plage d'identité. Il faut consulter la table [CP1252^Code Page 1252] pour trouver son octet entre `0x80` et `0x9F`, puis convertir en binaire."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_encode.ex:77
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Code point outside the Latin-1 range (beyond `U+00FF`)."
msgstr "Code point hors plage Latin-1 (au-delà de `U+00FF`)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:111
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Concatenate the 10 + 10 bits then add `0x10000` to recover the code point."
msgstr "On concatène les 10 + 10 bits puis on ajoute `0x10000` pour retrouver le code point."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:167
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Concatenate the 4 bytes (reordered as Big Endian) to reform the full 32-bit binary.\nIn UTF-32 this binary IS the code point - no marker to strip, no surrogate to recombine."
msgstr "On concatène les 4 octets (réordonnés en Big Endian) pour reformer le binaire complet sur 32 bits.\nEn UTF-32 ce binaire EST le code point - pas de marqueur à retirer, pas de surrogate à recombiner."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:109
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert 4 UTF-32 bytes into a Unicode code point, given the endianness."
msgstr "Convertis 4 octets UTF-32 en code point Unicode, en précisant l'endianness."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:94
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a Latin-1 (ISO 8859-1) byte into a Unicode code point. 1:1 mapping, perfect identity over `0x00` → `0xFF`."
msgstr "Convertis un octet Latin-1 (ISO 8859-1) en code point Unicode. Mapping 1:1, identité parfaite sur `0x00` → `0xFF`."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_encode.ex:95
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a Unicode code point into 4 UTF-32 bytes, with a chosen endianness."
msgstr "Convertis un code point Unicode en 4 octets UTF-32, avec choix de l'endianness."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:122
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a Unicode code point into UTF-16 bytes, with a chosen endianness."
msgstr "Convertis un code point Unicode en octets UTF-16, avec choix de l'endianness."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:134
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a Unicode code point into a single Windows-1252 (CP1252) byte."
msgstr "Convertis un code point Unicode en un seul octet Windows-1252 (CP1252)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_encode.ex:92
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a Unicode code point to a Latin-1 (ISO 8859-1) byte. 1:1 mapping over the `U+0000` → `U+00FF` range."
msgstr "Convertis un code point Unicode en octet Latin-1 (ISO 8859-1). Mapping 1:1 sur la plage `U+0000` → `U+00FF`."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:138
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a Windows-1252 (CP1252) byte into a Unicode code point."
msgstr "Convertis un octet Windows-1252 (CP1252) en code point Unicode."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:126
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert a sequence of UTF-16 bytes into a Unicode code point, given the endianness."
msgstr "Convertis une suite d'octets UTF-16 en code point Unicode, en précisant l'endianness."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_encode.ex:146
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Convert to 32-bit binary"
msgstr "Convertir en binaire sur 32 bits"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:104
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "E9, 0xE9, or 41"
msgstr "E9, 0xE9, ou 41"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:91
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Each code unit is read high-order byte first (`Big Endian`)."
msgstr "On lit chaque code unit avec l'octet de poids fort en premier (`Big Endian`)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:94
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Each code unit is read low-order byte first (`Little Endian`)."
msgstr "On lit chaque code unit avec l'octet de poids faible en premier (`Little Endian`)."

#: lib/app_web/components/sandbox_components.ex:83
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Endianness"
msgstr "Endianness"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:70
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:75
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Enter a hex byte."
msgstr "Entre un octet hex."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:199
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Extract the useful bits from each surrogate"
msgstr "Extraire les bits utiles des surrogates"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:174
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:155
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Given endianness"
msgstr "Endianness précisée"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:141
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Hex (with or without `0x`). UTF-16 takes 2 or 4 bytes per code point."
msgstr "Hex (avec ou sans `0x`). UTF-16 prend 2 ou 4 octets par code point."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:122
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Hex (with or without `0x`). UTF-32 takes exactly 4 bytes per code point."
msgstr "Hex (avec ou sans `0x`). UTF-32 prend exactement 4 octets par code point."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:150
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Hex (with or without `0x`). Windows-1252 encodes one character per byte."
msgstr "Hex (avec ou sans `0x`). Windows-1252 encode un caractère sur un seul octet."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:186
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Identify the code unit count"
msgstr "Identifier le nombre de code units"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:21
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:92
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Latin-1 sandbox (decode)"
msgstr "Sandbox Latin-1 (décodage)"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_encode.ex:22
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_encode.ex:90
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Latin-1 sandbox (encode)"
msgstr "Sandbox Latin-1 (encodage)"

#: lib/app_web/components/sandbox_components.ex:100
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Little Endian (LE)"
msgstr "Little Endian (LE)"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:173
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Pick the UTF-16 form"
msgstr "Choisir le format UTF-16"

#: lib/app_web/live/exercise_live.ex:387
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:164
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_encode.ex:137
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Pick the endianness"
msgstr "Choisir l'endianness"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:91
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `0x00` → `0x7F` - ASCII identity: the byte is its own code point."
msgstr "Plage `0x00` → `0x7F` - identité ASCII : l'octet est son propre code point."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:90
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `0x00` → `0x7F` - identical to ASCII (and to Latin-1)."
msgstr "Plage `0x00` → `0x7F` - identique à l'ASCII (et à Latin-1)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:95
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `0x80` → `0x9F` - the Microsoft extension. This is where Windows-1252 diverges from Latin-1: 27 printable characters (`€` at `0x80`, `™` at `0x99`, em-dash `—` at `0x97`, smart quotes, ...) instead of C1 controls."
msgstr "Plage `0x80` → `0x9F` - l'extension Microsoft. C'est ici que Windows-1252 diverge de Latin-1 : on a 27 caractères imprimables (`€` à `0x80`, `™` à `0x99`, l'em-dash `—` à `0x97`, les guillemets typographiques...) au lieu des contrôles C1."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:94
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `0x80` → `0x9F` - the Microsoft extension: 27 printable characters like `€`, `™`, `—`, smart quotes, ... This is where [CP1252^Code Page 1252] differs from Latin-1 (which has C1 controls in that slot). 5 bytes remain unassigned: `0x81`, `0x8D`, `0x8F`, `0x90`, `0x9D`."
msgstr "Plage `0x80` → `0x9F` - l'extension Microsoft : 27 caractères imprimables comme `€`, `™`, `—`, les guillemets typographiques... C'est là que [CP1252^Code Page 1252] diffère de Latin-1 (qui contient des contrôles C1 à cet endroit). 5 octets restent non assignés : `0x81`, `0x8D`, `0x8F`, `0x90`, `0x9D`."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:100
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `0xA0` → `0xFF` - Latin-1 identity: the byte is its own code point."
msgstr "Plage `0xA0` → `0xFF` - identité Latin-1 : l'octet est son propre code point."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:99
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `0xA0` → `0xFF` - identical to Latin-1 (accented characters, symbols)."
msgstr "Plage `0xA0` → `0xFF` - identique à Latin-1 (caractères accentués, symboles)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:85
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `U+0000` → `U+FFFF` - the [BMP^Basic Multilingual Plane], which covers most of the world's scripts. Fits in a single 16-bit code unit, 2 bytes."
msgstr "Plage `U+0000` → `U+FFFF` - le [BMP^Basic Multilingual Plane], qui couvre l'essentiel des écritures du monde. 1 code unit de 16 bits suffit, soit 2 octets."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:91
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Range `U+10000` → `U+10FFFF` - beyond the [BMP^Basic Multilingual Plane], in the supplementary planes (emojis, historic scripts, rare [CJK^Chinese, Japanese, Korean]...). Encoded as a surrogate pair: 2 code units = 4 bytes."
msgstr "Plage `U+10000` → `U+10FFFF` - au-delà du [BMP^Basic Multilingual Plane], dans les plans supplémentaires (emojis, scripts historiques, [CJK^Chinois, Japonais, Coréen] rare...). Encodé en paire de surrogates : 2 code units = 4 octets."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:187
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Read the byte value in binary"
msgstr "Lire la valeur de l'octet en binaire"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:143
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Read the byte's bits"
msgstr "Lire les bits de l'octet"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:190
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Read the value in binary"
msgstr "Lire la valeur en binaire"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:192
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Split for the surrogates"
msgstr "Découper pour les surrogates"

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:196
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Split the 20 bits into 2 packets of 10 bits.\nThe left 10 bits (high-order) form the high surrogate, the right 10 bits (low-order) form the low surrogate.\nEach 10-bit packet represents an integer between 0 and 1,023 (10 bits = 2¹⁰ = 1,024 values). Add it to the surrogate base: `0xD800` for the high, `0xDC00` for the low."
msgstr "On découpe les 20 bits en 2 paquets de 10 bits.\nLes 10 bits de gauche (poids forts) forment le high surrogate, les 10 bits de droite (poids faibles) forment le low surrogate.\nChaque paquet de 10 bits représente un entier entre 0 et 1 023 (10 bits = 2¹⁰ = 1 024 valeurs). On l'ajoute à la base du surrogate : `0xD800` pour le high, `0xDC00` pour le low."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_encode.ex:163
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Split the binary into 4 packets of 8 bits, then write each packet in hex.\nThe order of the 4 bytes depends on the chosen endianness."
msgstr "On découpe le binaire en 4 paquets de 8 bits, puis on écrit chaque paquet en hex.\nL'ordre des 4 octets dépend de l'endianness choisie."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:99
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Subtract `0x10000` and keep the remaining 20 bits."
msgstr "On retire `0x10000` puis on garde les 20 bits restants."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:203
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Subtract `0xD800` from the high surrogate (10 high bits) and `0xDC00` from the low surrogate (10 low bits)."
msgstr "Du high surrogate on retire `0xD800` (10 bits hauts), du low surrogate on retire `0xDC00` (10 bits bas)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:108
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The 16 bits of the code unit are the code point."
msgstr "Les 16 bits du code unit constituent directement le code point."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:105
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The 2 code units (high + low surrogate) yield 4 bytes, each code unit ordered by endianness."
msgstr "Les 2 code units (high + low surrogate) donnent 4 octets, chaque code unit ordonné selon l'endianness."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:88
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The 4 bytes are read high-order byte first (`Big Endian`)."
msgstr "On lit les 4 octets avec l'octet de poids fort en premier (`Big Endian`)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:92
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The 4 bytes are read low-order byte first (`Little Endian`). Mentally reverse the byte order before assembling the number."
msgstr "On lit les 4 octets avec l'octet de poids faible en premier (`Little Endian`). On inverse mentalement l'ordre des octets avant d'assembler le nombre."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_encode.ex:153
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The 8 bits form a single byte, i.e. `2` hex digits."
msgstr "Les 8 bits forment un seul octet, soit `2` chiffres hexadécimaux."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:199
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The binary byte becomes its 2-digit hex value."
msgstr "L'octet binaire devient sa valeur hex sur 2 chiffres."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:162
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The byte equals `%{decimal}` in decimal, i.e. `%{cp}` in Unicode notation. Latin-1 makes the byte value and the code point coincide over the whole range."
msgstr "L'octet vaut `%{decimal}` en décimal, soit `%{cp}` en notation Unicode. Latin-1 fait coïncider valeur d'octet et code point sur toute la plage."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:104
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The byte is `%{decimal}` in decimal, identical to its code point (ASCII range: pure identity). That's `%{cp}` in Unicode notation."
msgstr "L'octet vaut `%{decimal}` en décimal, identique à son code point (plage ASCII : pure identité). Soit `%{cp}` en notation Unicode."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:120
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The byte is `%{decimal}` in decimal, identical to its code point (Latin-1 range: pure identity). That's `%{cp}` in Unicode notation."
msgstr "L'octet vaut `%{decimal}` en décimal, identique à son code point (plage Latin-1 : pure identité). Soit `%{cp}` en notation Unicode."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:146
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The byte is directly the 8 bits of the code point (no marker to strip)."
msgstr "L'octet vaut directement les 8 bits du code point (pas de marqueur à retirer)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:112
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The byte is in the Microsoft extension. The [CP1252^Code Page 1252] table maps it to `%{cp}` (decimal `%{decimal}`). Classic trap: if you read this same byte as Latin-1, you get an invisible C1 control instead of a printable character."
msgstr "L'octet est dans l'extension Microsoft. La table [CP1252^Code Page 1252] le fait correspondre à `%{cp}` (décimal `%{decimal}`). C'est le piège classique : si on lit ce même octet comme Latin-1, on obtient un contrôle C1 invisible au lieu d'un caractère imprimable."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:74
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:79
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The byte is incomplete (odd number of hex digits)."
msgstr "L'octet est incomplet (nombre impair de chiffres hex)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_encode.ex:72
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The high-order byte comes first (`Big Endian`). The 4 bytes are written in the natural order of the number."
msgstr "L'octet de poids fort vient en premier (`Big Endian`). Les 4 octets s'écrivent dans l'ordre naturel du nombre."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:78
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The high-order byte of each code unit comes first (`Big Endian`)."
msgstr "L'octet de poids fort vient en premier dans chaque code unit (`Big Endian`)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_encode.ex:78
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The low-order byte comes first (`Little Endian`). The 4 bytes are written in reverse order from the number."
msgstr "L'octet de poids faible vient en premier (`Little Endian`). Les 4 octets s'écrivent dans l'ordre inverse du nombre."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:81
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The low-order byte of each code unit comes first (`Little Endian`)."
msgstr "L'octet de poids faible vient en premier dans chaque code unit (`Little Endian`)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_encode.ex:101
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The single code unit yields 2 bytes, ordered by endianness."
msgstr "L'unique code unit donne 2 octets, ordre déterminé par l'endianness."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:86
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This byte doesn't map to any character in Windows-1252. Either it's an unassigned byte (`0x81`, `0x8D`, `0x8F`, `0x90`, `0x9D`), or you entered more than one byte (CP1252 = 1 byte per character)."
msgstr "Cet octet ne donne aucun caractère en Windows-1252. Soit c'est un octet non assigné (`0x81`, `0x8D`, `0x8F`, `0x90`, `0x9D`), soit tu as saisi plusieurs octets (CP1252 = 1 octet par caractère)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:79
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This byte is not a valid Latin-1 byte."
msgstr "Cet octet ne forme pas un Latin-1 valide."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_encode.ex:85
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This code point isn't in the Windows-1252 table. Outside the ASCII and Latin-1 ranges, only 27 specific characters can be encoded."
msgstr "Ce code point n'existe pas dans la table Windows-1252. Au-delà des plages ASCII et Latin-1, seuls 27 caractères spécifiques sont encodables."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:86
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This sequence doesn't form a single UTF-16 code point. The same byte stream can be one valid code point in BE and multiple in LE (or vice versa)."
msgstr "Cette séquence ne forme pas un code point UTF-16 unique. Un même flux d'octets peut donner un code point valide en BE et plusieurs en LE (ou inversement)."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:83
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "This sequence doesn't form a valid UTF-32 code point. It needs exactly 4 bytes, and the value must be in `U+0000` → `U+10FFFF` excluding surrogates."
msgstr "Cette séquence ne forme pas un code point UTF-32 valide. Il faut exactement 4 octets, et la valeur doit être dans `U+0000` → `U+10FFFF` hors surrogates."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/latin1_decode.ex:77
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Too many bytes: Latin-1 encodes a code point in exactly 1 byte."
msgstr "Trop d'octets : Latin-1 encode un code point sur exactement 1 octet."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:82
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Too many bytes: UTF-16 encodes a single code point in 2 or 4 bytes."
msgstr "Trop d'octets : UTF-16 encode un seul code point sur 2 ou 4 octets."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf32_decode.ex:79
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Too many bytes: UTF-32 encodes a single code point in exactly 4 bytes."
msgstr "Trop d'octets : UTF-32 encode un seul code point sur exactement 4 octets."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/windows1252_decode.ex:82
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Too many bytes: Windows-1252 encodes a single character in one byte."
msgstr "Trop d'octets : Windows-1252 encode un seul caractère sur un seul octet."

#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:24
#: lib/app_web/live/sandbox/utf16_decode.ex:124
